output: Hmue Gyi is a researcher at the University of California, Berkeley. He is a recipient of the NSF CAREER award and the Google Faculty Award. His research interests include natural language processing, machine learning, and computational linguistics. He has published over 100 papers in top-tier conferences and journals, including ACL, EMNLP, NAACL, and NIPS. He is the co-author of the book "Natural Language Processing with Python" and the co-founder of the NLP community at Berkeley.
